article.headline: Montana 69, SE Missouri State 66
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. (AP) -- Kamarr Davis scored 15 points, leading Montana to a 69-66 victory over Southeast Missouri State on Thursday night. Kevin Criswell and Matt Martin added 13 points each for the Grizzlies (3-3). Montana outshot Southeast Missouri State 53 percent (28-for-53) to 47 percent (24-for-51) from the line, offsetting the Indians' advantage at the free throw line. Southeast Missouri State (2-4) was 13-for-20 on foul shots to Montana's 6-for-10. Dainmon Gonner led the Indians with 18 points, but missed a 3-point try in the closing seconds that would have forced overtime. Reggie Golson added 14 points, 14 rebounds and three blocked shots for Southeast Missouri State, which fell behind by nine points in the first 10 minutes and trailed 37-30 at the half.
